Sentencas: Pd-Y(2)O(3) stabilized ZrO(2) (YSZ) composite cathodes are prepared by conventional mechanical mixing and infiltration methods.
Titulo: Pd-YSZ composite cathodes for oxygen reduction reaction of intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In the case of infiltration, thermal decomposition and chemical reduction processes are used to form Pd particles on the YSZ scaffold.
Titulo: Pd-YSZ composite cathodes for oxygen reduction reaction of intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The phase structure, morphology and electrochemical performance of the Pd-YSZ composite cathodes are characterized by X-ray diffraction (XRD), scanning electron microscope (SEM), transmission electron microscope (TEM) and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS).
Titulo: Pd-YSZ composite cathodes for oxygen reduction reaction of intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The performance of mechanically mixed Pd-YSZ composite cathodes is inadequate due to significant growth and sporadical distribution of Pd particles.
Titulo: Pd-YSZ composite cathodes for oxygen reduction reaction of intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The 5 wt.% Pd-loaded cathode prepared by infiltration-thermal decomposition process shows the lowest polarization resistance, i.e. between 0.042 Omega cm(2) and 1.5 Omega cm(2) in the temperature range of 850-600 degrees C, benefited from the formation of nano-sized Pd particles and the presence of well connected Pd network.
Titulo: Pd-YSZ composite cathodes for oxygen reduction reaction of intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effect of Pd loading on the performance of the infiltrated-thermal decomposed Pd-YSZ composite cathodes is also evaluated, 5 wt.% Pd loading results in the lowest polarization resistances.
Titulo: Pd-YSZ composite cathodes for oxygen reduction reaction of intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
